thread.title: Gas prices stay the same in New Hampshire, national goes up

author: wcax.com
title: Gas prices stay the same in New Hampshire, national goes up
text:
CONCORD, N.H. (AP) - Gas prices in New Hampshire stayed the same in the past week, averaging $2.16 a gallon.
Gasbuddy.com, which surveyed 875 gas stations in the state, says that's 15 cents lower than the national average, which went up 2.7 cents to $2.31 a gallon.
Gas prices in New Hampshire are nearly $1.09 lower than they were a year ago, and 11.2 cents per gallon lower than a month ago.
The national average is 3.1 cents per gallon lower than it was a month ago and 88 cents per gallon lower than a year ago
